-- Hermitage to Feature at Sotheby’s Hong Kong Wine Sale
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2012-12-01T05:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-01/hermitage-to-feature-with-drc-at-sotheby-s-hong-kong-sale.html
Sotheby’s (BID)  holds a wine sale in Hong
Kong this week featuring Hermitage La Chapelle as well as
Romanee-Conti 1995 Domaine de la Romanee-Conti and Richebourg
1985 DRC Burgundies.  A three-bottle lot of Hermitage La Chapelle 1961 Paul
Jaboulet Aine and a three-liter jeroboam of Romanee-Conti 1995
DRC each carry an upper estimate of HK$400,000 ($51,600), while
a 12-bottle case of Richebourg 1985 DRC is estimated at as much
as HK$220,000, according to its online catalog.  Leading the Bordeaux section of its sale is a case of
Chateau Petrus 2000, estimated to fetch as much as HK$550,000,
and two separate lots of Chateau Petrus 2005, one a 12-bottle
case and the other six magnums, each estimated at as much as
HK$300,000.  Zachys is holding sales over three days in  New York  at the
end of this week, and taking the occasion to mark its 10th
anniversary.  Wines up for auction include Bordeaux first-growth Chateau
Haut-Brion 1961, La Tache 1990 DRC and a selection of Domaine
Leflaive from Burgundy and almost 100 lots of Italian producer
Gaja, including Barbaresco, Barolo and Brunello di Montalcino
wines.  Acker Merrall & Condit also holds a three-day sale in  Hong
Kong .  Following is a list of global wine sales taking place this
weekend and scheduled for the rest of this year. Dates may be
subject to revision, and links are to auction house sale
catalogs and websites.  
